      "preview": {
        "html": "<div class=\"kit-toast\"><strong>Copied</strong><span>Component source copied.</span></div>",
        "css": ".kit-toast{width:260px;border:1px solid #CBD5E1;border-radius:8px;background:#fff;padding:12px;box-shadow:0 8px 24px rgba(15,23,42,.08);font:13px Inter}.kit-toast strong{display:block}.kit-toast span{color:#64748B}"
      },
      "usage": "Use for confirmation that does not require a decision. Do not hide errors that need correction."
    }
  },
  "guidelines_markdown": "## Principles\n\n- Build product UI for repeated work: clear labels, visible state, compact controls, and fast scanning.\n- Prefer shadcn primitives for behavior and accessibility, then layer BlueKiwi tokens through Tailwind variables.\n- Keep repeated object cards at 8px radius or less; do not nest cards inside cards.\n- Every form control documents default, hover, focus-visible, disabled, and error states.\n- Every table/list surface documents loading, empty, error, populated, and edge states.\n- Use DESIGN.md for agent-readable guidance and adapters/package exports for implementation handoff.\n\n## Tailwind Mapping\n\nMap color tokens to CSS variables: background, foreground, card, primary, secondary, muted, accent, destructive, border, input, and ring. Keep semantic token names stable even when brand colors change.\n\n## shadcn Coverage\n\nThis seed intentionally covers the common shadcn surface area: Button, Input, Textarea, Select, Checkbox, RadioGroup, Switch, Card, Dialog, DropdownMenu, Tabs, Table, Badge, Alert, and Toast.",
  "skill_markdown": "Use this design system when building React/Tailwind/shadcn product interfaces, admin panels, registry viewers, settings screens, component libraries, and agent-facing tools. Load DESIGN.md first, then request adapters for implementation code."
}
